        <div>
          <div class="section-label">About</div>
          <h2>Bridging Theory &amp; Experiment</h2>
          <p>Dr. Yongmei Wang is a professor specializing in polymer physics and computational materials science. Her research group develops novel theoretical and computational approaches to understand the structure, dynamics, and thermodynamics of polymeric systems.</p>
          <p>Her work spans from fundamental polymer physics to the design of functional polymer materials with applications in energy storage, drug delivery, and sustainable materials.</p>
          <p>Dr. Wang has been recognized with multiple NSF and DOE grants, and is a fellow of the American Physical Society.</p>
          <div class="tag-list">
            <span class="tag">Polymer Physics</span>
            <span class="tag">Computational Modeling</span>
            <span class="tag">Molecular Dynamics</span>
            <span class="tag">Thermodynamics</span>
