  <!-- RESEARCH -->
  <section id="research">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-label">Research</div>
      <h2>Areas of Focus</h2>
      <p>Our group pursues interconnected lines of inquiry at the intersection of polymer physics, computational chemistry, and materials engineering.</p>
      <div class="research-grid">
        <div class="research-card">
          <div class="research-icon">üî¨</div>
          <h3>Polymer Dynamics</h3>
          <p>Investigating chain mobility, relaxation behavior, and viscoelastic properties in bulk and confined polymer systems using molecular simulation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="research-card">
          <div class="research-icon">‚ö°</div>
          <h3>Energy Materials</h3>
          <p>Designing polymer electrolytes and ion-conducting membranes for next-generation batteries and fuel cells through atomistic and coarse-grained modeling.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="research-card">
          <div class="research-icon">üß¨</div>
          <h3>Biopolymers</h3>
          <p>Studying protein‚Äìpolymer conjugates and bio-inspired macromolecular architectures for targeted drug delivery and biosensor applications.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="research-card">
          <div class="research-icon">üåø</div>
          <h3>Sustainable Polymers</h3>
          <p>Developing computational strategies to design biodegradable and recyclable polymers, supporting a circular materials economy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="research-card">
          <div class="research-icon">üìê</div>
          <h3>Polymer Blends &amp; Composites</h3>
          <p>Phase behavior and morphology control in multi-component polymer systems, from block copolymer self-assembly to nanocomposites.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="research-card">
          <div class="research-icon">üíª</div>
          <h3>Computational Methods</h3>
          <p>Advancing force field development, enhanced sampling algorithms, and machine learning potentials for accurate polymer simulation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

